        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 1:22PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 122 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tula, or 17 miles west of Pontotoc, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pontotoc, Ecru, Tula, Pinedale, Randolph, Etta, Thaxton, Toccopola,
Robbs, Hortontown, Esperanza, Cherry Creek, Bald Hill, Delay,
Buchannan, Matthews, Springville, Lafayette Springs, and Sarepta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
